OL,3,CFamilies of Chinook crash victims
OL,4,Cpress on with legal action against MoD
OL,6,F"The MoD is continuing to deceive our
OL,7,Ffamilies and disrespect our loved
OL,8,Fones' memories by claiming that the
OL,9,Fmany previous inquiries investigated
OL,10,Fall the facts, but we now know the
OL,11,Faircraft was not airworthy. They
OL,12,Fdidn't know half of what we know now.
OL,14,F"The Government may have sealed the
OL,15,Ffiles for 100 years, but we, the
OL,16,Ffamilies of those who died, are firmly
OL,17,Funited, strong and defiant, and we
OL,18,Fwill get to the truth, no matter what
OL,19,Fit takes."
