OL,6,FFollowing the crash, the Chinook's
OL,7,Fpilots, Flight Lieutenants Richard
OL,8,FCook and Jonathan Tapper, were accused
OL,9,Fof gross negligence, but this verdict
OL,10,Fwas overturned by the UK government 17
OL,11,Fyears later following a campaign by
OL,12,Fthe families.
OL,14,FA subsequent review by Lord Philip set
OL,15,Fout "numerous concerns" raised by
OL,16,Fthose who worked on the Chinooks, with
OL,17,Fthe MoD's testing centre at Boscombe
OL,18,FDown in Wiltshire declaring the
OL,19,FChinook Mk2 helicopters "unairworthy"
OL,20,Fprior to the crash.
