OL,3,CFamilies of Chinook crash victims
OL,4,Cpress on with legal action against MoD
OL,6,F"My mum, my brother, I and all the
OL,7,Ffamilies deserve the truth and the MoD
OL,8,Fmust repay the honour and integrity
OL,9,Fthat those on board had shown in their
OL,10,Fyears of service to their country.
OL,11,FThat's why we formed the Chinook
OL,12,FJustice Campaign and we will not rest
OL,13,Funtil we get the truth. If that takes
OL,14,Fa judge to rule in court, then so be
OL,15,Fit."
OL,17,FThe families, who have coalesced into
OL,18,Fthe Chinook Justice Campaign, said
OL,19,Ffailing to order a public inquiry is a
OL,20,Fbreach of the UK Government's human
OL,21,Frights obligations.
